<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I've tried to derive my own class from Zend_Auth_Result and add some more failure codes. But there is a code segment in Zend_Auth_Result::__constructor wich blocks me from doing that.</p>

<p>[code]
if ($code &lt; self::FAILURE_UNCATEGORIZED) {
    $code = self::FAILURE;
} elseif ($code &gt; self::SUCCESS ) {
    $code = 1;
}
[/code]</p>

<p>Because FAILURE_UNCATEGORIZED is -4, i can't use a negative value lower than that. If FAILURE_UNCATEGORIZED would be e.g. -65535 there would be enough values.</p>

